One' }, { name: 'Al-Khabir', meaning: 'The Acquainted' }, { name: 'Al-Halim', meaning: 'The Forbearing' }, { name: 'Al-Azim', meaning: 'The Magnificent' }, { name: 'Al-Ghafur', meaning: 'The Great meaning: 'The Incomparable' }, { name: 'Al-Baqi', meaning: 'The Ever-Surviving' }, { name: 'Al-Warith', meaning: 'The Inheritor' }, { name: 'Ar-Rashid', meaning: 'The Righteous Teacher' }, { name: 'As-Sabur', meaning: 'The Patient' }, ]; const AllahIsimleri = () => { const [translatedNames, setTranslatedNames] = useState([]); useEffect(() => { const translateNames = async () => { try { const responses = await Promise.all(allahNames.map(name => axios.post('http://localhost:5000/translate', { text: name.meaning, target_lang: 'tr', // Translate to Turkish }) )); const translations = responses.map(response => response.data.text); const translatedNamesWithMeanings = allahNames.map((name, index) => ({ ...name, translatedMeaning: translations[index], frame: `Frame#${index + 1}`, })); setTranslatedNames(translatedNamesWithMeanings); } catch (error) { console.error('Translation Error:', error); } }; translateNames(); }, []); return (
{translatedNames.map((name, index) => (

{name.frame} - {name.name}

{name.translatedMeaning}

))}
); }; export default AllahIsimleri;
